# React Islands in Astro

## When to Use React

Use React components (islands) only for:
- **Forms** with validation and state (ContactForm, Newsletter)
- **Calculators** with dynamic computation (CostCalculator)
- **Interactive widgets** (Carousels, Accordions with animation)
- **Third-party integrations** requiring JS (HubSpot embed)

**Do NOT use React for:**
- Static content display
- Navigation (use Astro + View Transitions)
- Simple show/hide (use CSS or vanilla JS)

## Client Directives

```astro
<!-- Load when visible in viewport (recommended for below-fold) -->
<ContactForm client:visible />

<!-- Load immediately on page load -->
<CriticalWidget client:load />

<!-- Load when browser is idle -->
<Analytics client:idle />

<!-- Load only on specific media query -->
<MobileMenu client:media="(max-width: 768px)" />

<!-- Never hydrate - render only (for SEO content) -->
<StaticPreview client:only="react" />
```

## Component Structure

```tsx
// src/components/islands/ContactForm.tsx
import { useState } from 'react';

interface ContactFormProps {
  hubspotFormId?: string;
  successMessage?: string;
}

export default function ContactForm({ 
  hubspotFormId,
  successMessage = 'Thanks! We\'ll be in touch.' 
}: ContactFormProps) {
  const [isSubmitting, setIsSubmitting] = useState(false);
  const [isSuccess, setIsSuccess] = useState(false);

  const handleSubmit = async (e: React.FormEvent) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    setIsSubmitting(true);
    // Form logic...
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="space-y-4">
      {/* Form fields */}
    </form>
  );
}
```

## Styling React Components

Use Tailwind classes directly - they work the same as in Astro:

```tsx
export default function Button({ children, variant = 'primary' }) {
  const baseStyles = 'px-6 py-3 font-semibold rounded-sm transition-colors duration-150';
  const variants = {
    primary: 'bg-[var(--color-primary)] text-white hover:bg-[var(--color-primary-light)]',
    secondary: 'border-2 border-[var(--color-primary)] text-[var(--color-primary)]',
  };

  return (
    <button className={`${baseStyles} ${variants[variant]}`}>
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}
```

## Passing Data from Astro

```astro
---
// Fetch data at build time
const pricingTiers = await fetchPricing();
---

<!-- Pass as props to React island -->
<CostCalculator 
  client:visible 
  tiers={pricingTiers}
  currency="USD"
/>
```

## File Organization

```
src/components/islands/
├── ContactForm.tsx      # HubSpot integration
├── CostCalculator.tsx   # Pricing calculator
├── ProductDemo.tsx      # Interactive product preview
├── VideoPlayer.tsx      # Lazy-loaded video
└── ThemeToggle.tsx      # Dark mode switch
```

## State Management

For simple islands, use React hooks (`useState`, `useReducer`).

For shared state across islands, consider:
- URL search params (shareable state)
- `nanostores` (lightweight, framework-agnostic)

```tsx
// src/stores/theme.ts
import { atom } from 'nanostores';
export const themeStore = atom<'light' | 'dark'>('light');

// In React component
import { useStore } from '@nanostores/react';
import { themeStore } from '../stores/theme';

const theme = useStore(themeStore);
```
